tourBios.carHigh: 2014: Finished T8 at PGA TOUR Canada Qualifying School in California to earn rookie card for 2014...After an uneven start to the season, posted four rounds in the 60s at the Wildfire Invitational to finish solo third, one shot back of champion Nate McCoy and Michael Gligic.
tourBios.otherCarHigh: 2010 Freshman All-SEC at the University of Tennessee...2009 AJGA Honorable Mention All-America.
tourBios.personal: A car and motorcycle enthusiast, biggest thrill outside golf is working on his motorcycle. Bucket list includes riding motorcycle cross country and racing in a NASCAR event...Favorite city to visit is Las Vegas...Favorite course is Pinehurst and favorite professional teams are the Denver Broncos and the Oklahoma City Thunder.

dyn.dynResults: His best finish on the Mackenzie Tour-PGA T was 3rd in 2014 at the Wildfire Invitational presented by PC Financial.
dyn.dynStats: He ranks 87th in Par Breakers on the Mackenzie Tour-PGA TOUR Canada.
